author: Nexcell Pride
text:
As curiosity, Piyoko returned as drawing. 
That Piyoko or Hiyoko-hane was born as a drawing made by Rushia herself in 2020 April 19th.
Cover Corp. (Hololive) and Rushia's followers, including fandeads, were charmed with Rushia's companion and Piyoko was quickly accepted. Days after, Yasuyuki-sensei accepted Piyoko as Rushia's partner, but she wasn't included at Live2D until 2021 January 22nd.
Now for some reasons, Rushia sets Piyoko's drawing instead of setting at top of her head (Live2D maybe needs corrections, along with Nekomimi and Crown conflict) 

Today's mission was bringing bunnies to Usada Buildings.
At previous streams, Rushia captured bunnies, one of them was black (Kurousagi)
But the harder part is... How to carry them?
Maybe walking was the only way to carry them instead of flying, because:
— Needs a carrot to lure them
— If flying, needs water to soft landing, but for flying needs fireworks. 
In resume, too harder to carry many animals.
Handicap: If night cames and creatures like zombies, creepers and others start attacking player.

0:37:57 Rushia noticed about Peko-chan's build-up: a dual house-office built dedicated to Uparupa duet's 2nd Anniversary. (Peko-chan debuted at 2019 July 17th, Rushia made her debut at following day, and both debuted as duet at 2019 July 20th with their first gameplay and collab) 

At 0:38:32, memories about "Manaita" sign made by Peko-chan (Maybe at first days at this version of Holoserver)
Maybe that sign was used to indicate where's Rushia's house, because house's function was as Workshop and item provisions. 

And later, the mission: building a Usagi farm and hatchery. 

:_ちょうちょ: Uruha Rushia's Original Character Design by Yasuyuki-sensei
(For more information, please contact him at Twitter as "yasu00kamiki" and "kamikirebasami") 
:_ハート:Live2D modeling by Tou Ilie 

Special Mark: 2:30:13 :_きゅん:
